<section xml:id="sec-6-4-Compounding_Interest" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Compounding Interest</title>
    <p><em>Compounding Interest</em> covers problems associated with continuously compounded interest. 
        It uses the model <m>A = P e^{r t}</m>. Compounding interest in discrete time steps, 
        for example, compounding interest annually is not addressed here. This lesson assumes an 
        understanding of logarithms when trying to solve for the rate or time. Information on 
        logarithms can be found in lesson on <xref ref="sec-6-1-The_Logarithm_Function" text="title"/>
         and <xref ref="sec-6-2-Properties_of_Logarithms" text="title"/>.</p>
        
